entator who should have known better.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a commentator\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having secured gold in thewomen's 4x100m freestyle relay, the Australian quartet of Emma McKeon, Shayna Jack, Mollie O'Callaghan and Meg Harris made their way out of the Paris Aquatic Centre.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999995986964573, \"rank\": 4.00824199255924e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1000, \"end\": 1011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma McKeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shayna Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mollie O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Meg Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\"}, {\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999956344254, \"rank\": 4.365474155210831e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thewomen's 4x100m freestyle relay\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was then thatEurosport commentator Bob Ballardsaid: \\\"Well, the women, just finishing up.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.7149176451483255, \"rank\": 0.2908733849029316, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Well, the women\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You know what women are like\\u2026 hanging around, doing their makeup\\u2026\\\" The outrageous comment went viral instantly, and Ballard was subsequently removed from Eurosport's broadcasting roster.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}, {\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4822632793192977e-17, \"text\": \"Eurosport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"their makeup\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"The outrageous comment\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports commentary is an art form.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports commentary\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"an art form\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It takes a sharp mind and a keen eye to encapsulate a moment for an audience, to translate the action in a sports arena to the listener or viewer.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sharp mind\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"a keen eye\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"an audience\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"a sports arena\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"the listener\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ballard has had a long and successful career in commentating.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long and successful career\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BBC has described him as \\\"a stalwart of global sports coverage since the 1980s, reporting on multiple Olympic Games and world championships\\\".\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1637, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9999337355453211, \"rank\": 5.00179445738997e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stalwart\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"global sports coverage\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"world championships\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, with all that experience behind him, what part of Ballard suddenly made him feel it was acceptable to make such an obviously sexist comment?\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all that experience\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1808}, {\"ngram\": \"what part\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"such an obviously sexist comment\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Misogynist language is not new to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Misogynist language\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Rio Games in 2016,Mail Onlinedescribed American swimmer Katie Ledecky as \\\"the female Michael Phelps\\\".\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.194412964554915e-55, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"2016,Mail\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WhenUS gymnast Simone Bilesgave an incredible performance on the uneven bars, an NBC commentator gave a backhanded compliment, saying: \\\"I think she might even go higher than the men.\\\"\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2168, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.998917675219055, \"rank\": 0.001083496271269805, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an incredible performance\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"the uneven bars\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"a backhanded compliment\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2212}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some comedians appear to think that female Olympians are fair game.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some comedians\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"female Olympians\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"fair game\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2012 London Games, US TV host Conan O'Brien tweeted that weightlifter Holley Mangold would \\\"bring home the gold- and four guys against their will\\\".\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\", \"score\": 0.9999999912183739, \"rank\": 8.781423266384323e-09, \"text\": \"Conan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\"}, {\"begin\": 2417, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Holley Mangold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2012 London Games\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold- and four guys\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was during Beijing 2008 thatFrankie Boylefirst made his now infamous jibes about gold-medal swimmerRebecca Adlington, saying she \\\"looks pretty weird... like someone who's looking at themselves in the back of a spoon\\\".\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995375219, \"rank\": 4.624303255091881e-10, \"text\": \"Beijing 2008\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2609, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"score\": 0.9999917386944804, \"rank\": 6.313147560071048e-06, \"text\": \"Adlington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boylefirst\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"his now infamous jibes\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2576}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"a spoon\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a study by Cambridge University Press, sexist thinking runs through the Games.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9319011684590155, \"rank\": 0.07307516488427633, \"text\": \"Cambridge University Press\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a study\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2741}, {\"ngram\": \"sexist thinking\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2788}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchers analysed millions of words relating to men and women and Olympic sports in the Cambridge international corpus (CIC) and the sports corpus - enormous databases of news articles and social media posts.\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2936, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\", \"score\": 0.974142566594674, \"rank\": 0.01164680450662347, \"text\": \"CIC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Researchers\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2824}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"words\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2851}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2877}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2896}, {\"ngram\": \"enormous databases\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"news articles\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"social media posts\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The study found that language around female competitors focussed disproportionately on appearance, clothes and personal lives.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The study\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3034}, {\"ngram\": \"language\", \"from\": 3046, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"female competitors\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3080}, {\"ngram\": \"appearance\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"clothes\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3131}, {\"ngram\": \"personal lives\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Common word combinations for women included \\\"aged\\\", \\\"older\\\", \\\"pregnant\\\" and \\\"married\\\" or \\\"unmarried\\\".\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Common word combinations\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, top word combinations for male athletes included \\\"fastest\\\", \\\"strong\\\", \\\"big\\\" and \\\"great\\\".\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3265}, {\"ngram\": \"top word combinations\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3288}, {\"ngram\": \"male athletes\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can think of several common examples of such casual sexism in sports reporting.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several common examples\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3395}, {\"ngram\": \"such casual sexism\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3417}, {\"ngram\": \"sports reporting\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you listen out for it, you will hear the word \\\"girls\\\" often used as a descriptor of women competing in sport.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3487}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"girls\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3494}, {\"ngram\": \"a descriptor\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3522}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3531}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But can you remember the last time you heard a group of sportsmen being referred to as boys?\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3644, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last time\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3586}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"sportsmen\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3617}, {\"ngram\": \"boys\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, when certain sports are discussed in the media, it is often assumed that the sport being mentioned in the report is the men's game.\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"certain sports\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3675}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3702}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3738}, {\"ngram\": \"the report\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3768}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's game\", \"from\": 3772, \"to\": 3786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How often do we hear the media refer to \\\"women's football\\\", whereas men's football is just \\\"football\\\"?\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 3809, \"to\": 3818}, {\"ngram\": \"women's football\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3845}, {\"ngram\": \"men's football\", \"from\": 3856, \"to\": 3870}, {\"ngram\": \"just \\\"football\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the dial has definitely moved.\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dial\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The proportion of female athletes competing has increased in every Olympic Games since 1964, when it was 13.2 per cent.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The proportion\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3946}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 3950, \"to\": 3965}, {\"ngram\": \"every Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4012}, {\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By Rio 2016, it was 45 per cent.\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only now do we finally have a 50:50 ratio.\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4127, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 50:50 ratio\", \"from\": 4113, \"to\": 4126}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Female participation in sports has increased, making the media more aware of its responsibility when covering female athletes.\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4255, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Female participation\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4149}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4153, \"to\": 4159}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4191}, {\"ngram\": \"its responsibility\", \"from\": 4206, \"to\": 4224}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that major broadcasters such as Eurosport act swiftly when Ballardisms occur is proof of real progress.\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fact\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4264}, {\"ngram\": \"major broadcasters\", \"from\": 4270, \"to\": 4288}, {\"ngram\": \"Eurosport\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4306}, {\"ngram\": \"Ballardisms\", \"from\": 4324, \"to\": 4335}, {\"ngram\": \"proof\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4350}, {\"ngram\": \"real progress\", \"from\": 4354, \"to\": 4367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As coverage improves, sexist language and comments are more noticeable when they happen.\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"coverage\", \"from\": 4372, \"to\": 4380}, {\"ngram\": \"sexist language\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4406}, {\"ngram\": \"comments\", \"from\": 4411, \"to\": 4419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I bet this will not be the last bit of casual sexism we hear during these Olympics.\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last bit\", \"from\": 4486, \"to\": 4498}, {\"ngram\": \"casual sexism\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4515}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Viewers, on your marks\\u2026 Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4623, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3375816258496497e-22, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Viewers\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4554}, {\"ngram\": \"your marks\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4607}, {\"ngram\": \"their replies\", \"from\": 4650, \"to\": 4663}, {\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4687}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 4703, \"to\": 4715}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4727}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4763}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 4772, \"to\": 4784}]}]}"